<TITLE> BSF kills one in Naogaon </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Naogaon, Dec 14(bdnews24.com)Indian border guards early on Monday shot dead a Bangladeshi along Hapania border of Sapahar Upazila in Naogaon, police said. Police and BDR sources said 40-year old Mofizul Islam of Adalpur village under Sapahar Upazila was returning home after buying a cow from a cattle market adjacent to the border. Border Security Force members of Pantapur camp in India opened fire on him and he died on the spot. They dragged the body of Mofiz inside India, the sources said. Major Manzur of 46 Rifles Battalion in Naogaon confirmed the incident, adding that they had protested the killing and asked the BSF to return the body. bdn
